## What does $R^2$ not measure?

::: columns
::: {.column width="37%"}
-   $R^2$ is not a measure of the magnitude of the slope of the
    regression line

    -   Example: can have $R^2 = 1$ for many different slopes!!

-   $R^2$ is not a measure of the appropriateness of the straight-line
    model

    -   Example: figure
